[
  "Wilma Tisch owes her fortune to her late husband Laurence (d. 2003) and his brother Bob, who started Loews Corp as a New Jersey hotel venture in 1946.",
  "Wilma's son James is the president and CEO of Loews, which now has interests in drilling, natural gas pipelines and insurance.",
  "Until her death in Nov. 2017 her sister-in law Joan Tisch was also a billionaire; Wilma's son Andrew co-chairs Loews' board with Joan's son Andrew.",
  "At NYU, the Tisch family donated funds to support the Tisch School of the Arts and the Tisch Hospital at Langone Medical Center.",
  "Wilma donates some of her Loews shares annually to her children's charitable foundations, as well as her own."
]